{% comment %} {% assign number_of_comments = article.comments_count %}
{% if comment and comment.created_at %}
  {% assign number_of_comments = article.comments_count %}
{% endif %}

<h1>{{ article.title }}</h1>
{% capture author %}<strong>{{ article.author }}</strong>{% endcapture %}
{% capture date %}<time datetime="{{ article.published_at | date: '%Y-%m-%d' }}">{{ article.published_at | date: format: 'month_day_year' }}</time>{% endcapture %}
{{ article.author }} @ {{ article.created_at }}

<div>{{ article.content }}</div>
{% if blog.comments_enabled? %}
  <h2>{{ number_of_comments }} comments</h2>
  {% paginate article.comments by 5 %}
    {% for comment in article.comments %}
      <div>
        <div>{{ comment.content }}</div>
        {{ comment.author }} @ {{ comment.created_at }}
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
    {% if paginate.pages > 1 %}
      {{ paginate | default_pagination }}
    {% endif %}
  {% endpaginate %}

  <div>
    {% form 'new_comment', article %}
      {{ form.errors | default_errors }}
      <label for="CommentAuthor">name</label>
      <input type="text" name="comment[author]" id="CommentAuthor" placeholder="name" value="{{ form.author }}" autocapitalize="words">

      <label for="CommentEmail">email</label>
      <input type="email" name="comment[email]" id="CommentEmail" placeholder="email" value="{{ form.email }}" autocorrect="off" autocapitalize="off">

      <label for="CommentBody">message</label>
      <textarea name="comment[body]" id="CommentBody" placeholder="message">{{ form.body }}</textarea>

      <input type="submit" value="post">
    {% endform %}
  </div>
{% endif %} {% endcomment %}

<div class="content-wrapper container">
  <div class="article-container">
  <article class="article-content">
      <div>
          <h1 class="article-title">{{article.title }}</h1>
          <p class="article-subtitle">By {{article.author }} - {{article.created_at }}</p>
      </div>

      <figure>
          <img src="{{article.image | img_url }}" alt="Web Development" class="article-image">
          <figcaption>The rapid evolution of web technologies.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <section class="article-body">
          <p>
              In 2024, web development has become one of the most in-demand skills in the technology industry. Whether you're looking to build a personal project or start a new career, learning web development can open doors to numerous opportunities.
          </p>
          <p>
              This article covers the key reasons why learning web development is essential today, along with tips for getting started. With the increasing reliance on digital tools and platforms, web developers play a critical role in shaping the future of online experiences.
          </p>
          <h2>Why Learn Web Development?</h2>
          <p>
              The internet is now an integral part of daily life, and every business or organization needs a strong online presence. Web developers are responsible for designing and maintaining websites, web applications, and services that people interact with every day.
          </p>
          <blockquote>
              "Web development is one of the fastest-growing fields, with a projected 8% growth rate through 2028." – Bureau of Labor Statistics
          </blockquote>
          <h2>Getting Started with Web Development</h2>
          <p>
              Whether you're a complete beginner or someone with some coding experience, there are many paths you can take to become a web developer. It's important to start with the basics of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. From there, you can explore more advanced frameworks like React, Vue, and Angular.
          </p>
      </section>

      <footer class="article-footer">
          <p>Written by Jane Doe. If you enjoyed this article, check out more on our <a href="#">blog</a>.</p>
      </footer>
  </article>
</div>

   <aside class="sidebar">
  <h2>Related Articles</h2>
  <ul class="article-list">
      <li><a href="#">10 Tips for Learning JavaScript Faster</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Why CSS Grid is the Future of Web Layouts</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Introduction to React: A Beginner's Guide</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Mastering Flexbox: Building Flexible Layouts</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Understanding REST APIs in Web Development</a></li>
  </ul>
   </aside>
</div>


